    %h2 Basic Promotion
    %p
      Androcommerce proposes great start as freemium. Here you're starting your ecommerce startup with personal Android storefront app. This app is located on dedicated page of Andocmmerce Market - website similar to Google's Play Market.
      %br
      Your storefront app has dedicated url for download. Also each product submitted by you to your storefront receives dedicated page under Androcommerce Market too.
      %br
      So nothing stops you from promoting both your storefront app and your products using Twitter, Facebook, G+ or any other social channels.<br/>You can do it for free. Just create enthusiastic group around your storefront and be in touch with your followers.

.row
  .col-xs-12.col-sm-4
    = image_tag "office_image.jpg",  class: 'img-responsive img-center img-padding-top'
  .col-xs-12.col-sm-8
    %h2 Use Mobile App Markets
    %p
      The next step is maintaining your own brand inside existing mobile app markets
      %br 
      Create Android Developer account and upload your storefront there. Pay special attention to audience of your app. If you are local vendor - reduce your audience to City or region. This will rank your app above global concurents.
      %br 
      Register Apple Developer Account. Add DroidBrew representative as your team member. It will give us ability to upload your storefront to App Store. And use the same advise as for Plqy Marlet: use your locality as additional promotion force.

